	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64247766"><p>And just to add to that, I would note that nearly every time I've helped someone with a computer that was crashing constantly, bad RAM was at fault.  ECC would have made it possible for the OS to detect those problems and alert the user that their RAM was defective.  Instead, some of them had suffered for years, thinking that their computer's behavior was normal.</p><p>That's why ECC should really be an "everyone" thing, not a "server" thing.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64247766">
