		<div id="comment_body_64248324"><p>Some time ago, I read that more and more with RAM density increases, the RAM sticks had ECC internally, and a quick search seems to <a href="https://www.synopsys.com/designware-ip/technical-bulletin/error-correction-code-ddr.html" title="synopsys.com">confirm</a> [synopsys.com] it:</p><p><div class="quote"><p>For every 128 bits of data, DDR5 DRAMs has 8 additional bits for ECC storage.</p></div><p>Which means that it doesn't even cost significantly less to make non-ECC RAM, it's just crippled by lacking the interface on the bus.</p></div>
