	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64247930"><p>Once memory sizes get big the statistics don't look great for those running without ECC. If apps simply crashed on a bit error it wouldn't be a big deal. But introducing subtle corruption that an app later writes to disk can lead to a tech support nightmare for users. And costs software vendors millions in needless support calls.</p></div>
